<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Use a background/bitmap/wallpaper for a skin?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7229&amp;p=31037#p31037"><![CDATA[
That &quot;can't pinch an inch&quot; guy has got to be the best pixture to use for picture menu.<br />There are no highlights. All the text is readable. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />That would be a good option to have added,<br />but dynamic picture option would have to have some way of making it seamless at the column 1/2 border junction.<br />With Jcee picture menu, the two inner slices don't stretch and shrink, along with rest of picture. <br />This leaves distortion in that area where lines don't line up.<br />People have asked me how to get rid of that. Only way is make the inside border slices 0, or 1 pixel.<br />If Ivo can figure out a way to eliminate the slices interacting with the picture, that would be great.<br /><br /><br />I have'nt looked at Metallic skin for awhile. Can't you just make an emblem mask for the whole menu?<br /><br />Last thing. Whatever is going on in the picture looks like a a great effect.<br />Where there is part on left side, left top, and left bottom,<br />that the frame I guess has the the repeated tile effect of the right picture. It's like a reflection effect. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> <br />If the right middle part has same look to match, would be super.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Tue Jan 03, 2017 10:47 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
