<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7229&amp;p=31034#p31034"><![CDATA[
How to use an image as the background for the entire menu of two columns and have the image stretched dynamically to the height and width of the menu?<br /><br />The two ways I know are:<br />1. To use Jcee's skin: <!-- l --><a class="postlink-local" href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=5622">viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=5622</a><!-- l --><br />2. To use the Metallic skin and specify image for first and second column.<br /><br />But I want a simple GUI option in all of the skins to specify a bitmap and have it stretch to fit automatically, like Jcee's AeroGlassZ skin.<br /><br />Currently I am using the Metallic skin's options but it is not easy to align the left and right column images like only a continuous stretchable image can do:<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Tue Jan 03, 2017 8:09 am</p><hr />
